127struct PlayerSpell
128{
129 PlayerSpellState State : 7; // UPPER CASE TO CAUSE CONSOLE ERRORS (CHECK EVERY USAGE)!
130 bool Active : 1; // UPPER CASE TO CAUSE CONSOLE ERRORS (CHECK EVERY USAGE)! lower rank of a spell are not useable, but learnt
131 uint8 specMask : 8;
132 bool IsInSpec(uint8 spec) { return (specMask & (1 << spec)); }
133};
134
135struct PlayerTalent
136{
137 PlayerSpellState State : 8; // UPPER CASE TO CAUSE CONSOLE ERRORS (CHECK EVERY USAGE)!
138 uint8 specMask : 8;
139 uint32 talentID;
140 bool inSpellBook;
141 bool IsInSpec(uint8 spec) { return (specMask & (1 << spec)); }
142};

180// Spell modifier (used for modify other spells)
181struct SpellModifier
182{
183 SpellModifier(Aura* _ownerAura = nullptr) : op(SPELLMOD_DAMAGE), type(SPELLMOD_FLAT), charges(0), mask(), ownerAura(_ownerAura) {}
184 SpellModOp op : 8;
185 SpellModType type : 8;
186 int16 charges : 16;
187 int32 value{0};
188 flag96 mask;
189 uint32 spellId{0};
190 Aura* const ownerAura;
191};

249#define ACTION_BUTTON_ACTION(X) (uint32(X) & 0x00FFFFFF)
250#define ACTION_BUTTON_TYPE(X) ((uint32(X) & 0xFF000000) >> 24)
251#define MAX_ACTION_BUTTON_ACTION_VALUE (0x00FFFFFF+1)
252
253struct ActionButton
254{
255 ActionButton() = default;
256
257 uint32 packedData{0};
258 ActionButtonUpdateState uState{ACTIONBUTTON_NEW};
259
260 // helpers
261 [[nodiscard]] ActionButtonType GetType() const { return ActionButtonType(ACTION_BUTTON_TYPE(packedData)); }
262 [[nodiscard]] uint32 GetAction() const { return ACTION_BUTTON_ACTION(packedData); }
263 void SetActionAndType(uint32 action, ActionButtonType type)
264 {
265 uint32 newData = action | (uint32(type) << 24);
266 if (newData != packedData || uState == ACTIONBUTTON_DELETED)
267 {
268 packedData = newData;
269 if (uState != ACTIONBUTTON_NEW)
270 uState = ACTIONBUTTON_CHANGED;
271 }
272 }
273};
274
275#define MAX_ACTION_BUTTONS 144 //checked in 3.2.0

426struct Runes
427{
428 RuneInfo runes[MAX_RUNES];
429 uint8 runeState; // mask of available runes
430 RuneType lastUsedRune;
431
432 void SetRuneState(uint8 index, bool set = true)
433 {
434 if (set)
435 runeState |= (1 << index); // usable
436 else
437 runeState &= ~(1 << index); // on cooldown
438 }
439};

1448 [[nodiscard]] uint16 FindQuestSlot(uint32 quest_id) const;
1449 [[nodiscard]] uint32 GetQuestSlotQuestId(uint16 slot) const { return GetUInt32Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_ID_OFFSET); }
1450 [[nodiscard]] uint32 GetQuestSlotState(uint16 slot) const { return GetUInt32Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_STATE_OFFSET); }
1451 [[nodiscard]] uint16 GetQuestSlotCounter(uint16 slot, uint8 counter) const { return (uint16)(GetUInt64Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_COUNTS_OFFSET) >> (counter * 16)); }
1452 [[nodiscard]] uint32 GetQuestSlotTime(uint16 slot) const { return GetUInt32Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_TIME_OFFSET); }
1453 void SetQuestSlot(uint16 slot, uint32 quest_id, uint32 timer = 0)
1454 {
1455 SetUInt32Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_ID_OFFSET, quest_id);
1456 SetUInt32Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_STATE_OFFSET, 0);
1457 SetUInt32Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_COUNTS_OFFSET, 0);
1458 SetUInt32Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_COUNTS_OFFSET + 1, 0);
1459 SetUInt32Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_TIME_OFFSET, timer);
1460 }
1461 void SetQuestSlotCounter(uint16 slot, uint8 counter, uint16 count)
1462 {
1463 uint64 val = GetUInt64Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_COUNTS_OFFSET);
1464 val &= ~((uint64)0xFFFF << (counter * 16));
1465 val |= ((uint64)count << (counter * 16));
1466 SetUInt64Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_COUNTS_OFFSET, val);
1467 }
1468 void SetQuestSlotState(uint16 slot, uint32 state) { SetFlag(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_STATE_OFFSET, state); }
1469 void RemoveQuestSlotState(uint16 slot, uint32 state) { RemoveFlag(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_STATE_OFFSET, state); }
1470 void SetQuestSlotTimer(uint16 slot, uint32 timer) { SetUInt32Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_TIME_OFFSET, timer); }
1471 void SwapQuestSlot(uint16 slot1, uint16 slot2)
1472 {
1473 for (int i = 0; i < MAX_QUEST_OFFSET; ++i)
1474 {
1475 uint32 temp1 = GetUInt32Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + MAX_QUEST_OFFSET * slot1 + i);
1476 uint32 temp2 = GetUInt32Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + MAX_QUEST_OFFSET * slot2 + i);
1477
1478 SetUInt32Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + MAX_QUEST_OFFSET * slot1 + i, temp2);
1479 SetUInt32Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + MAX_QUEST_OFFSET * slot2 + i, temp1);
1480 }
1481 }

1632 void AddMItem(Item* it)
1633 {
1634 ASSERT(it);

2944
2945// "the bodies of template functions must be made available in a header file"
2946template <class T> T Player::ApplySpellMod(uint32 spellId, SpellModOp op, T& basevalue, Spell* spell, bool temporaryPet)
2947{
2948 SpellInfo const* spellInfo = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(spellId);
2949 if (!spellInfo)
2950 {
2951 return 0;
2952 }
2953
2954 float totalmul = 1.0f;
2955 int32 totalflat = 0;
2956
2957 auto calculateSpellMod = [&](SpellModifier* mod)
2958 {
2959 // xinef: temporary pets cannot use charged mods of owner, needed for mirror image QQ they should use their own auras
2960 if (temporaryPet && mod->charges != 0)
2961 {
2962 return;
2963 }
2964
2965 if (mod->type == SPELLMOD_FLAT)
2966 {
2967 // xinef: do not allow to consume more than one 100% crit increasing spell
2968 if (mod->op == SPELLMOD_CRITICAL_CHANCE && totalflat >= 100)
2969 {
2970 return;
2971 }
2972
2973 int32 flatValue = mod->value;
2974
2975 // SPELL_MOD_THREAT - divide by 100 (in packets we send threat * 100)
2976 if (mod->op == SPELLMOD_THREAT)
2977 {
2978 flatValue /= 100;
2979 }
2980
2981 totalflat += flatValue;
2982 }
2983 else if (mod->type == SPELLMOD_PCT)
2984 {
2985 // skip percent mods for null basevalue (most important for spell mods with charges)
2986 if (basevalue == T(0) || totalmul == 0.0f)
2987 {
2988 return;
2989 }
2990
2991 // special case (skip > 10sec spell casts for instant cast setting)
2992 if (mod->op == SPELLMOD_CASTING_TIME && basevalue >= T(10000) && mod->value <= -100)
2993 {
2994 return;
2995 }
2996 // xinef: special exception for surge of light, dont affect crit chance if previous mods were not applied
2997 else if (mod->op == SPELLMOD_CRITICAL_CHANCE && spell && !HasSpellMod(mod, spell))
2998 {
2999 return;
3000 }
3001 // xinef: special case for backdraft gcd reduce with backlast time reduction, dont affect gcd if cast time was not applied
3002 else if (mod->op == SPELLMOD_GLOBAL_COOLDOWN && spell && !HasSpellMod(mod, spell))
3003 {
3004 return;
3005 }
3006
3007 // xinef: those two mods should be multiplicative (Glyph of Renew)
3008 if (mod->op == SPELLMOD_DAMAGE || mod->op == SPELLMOD_DOT)
3009 {
3010 totalmul *= CalculatePct(1.0f, 100.0f + mod->value);
3011 }
3012 else
3013 {
3014 totalmul += CalculatePct(1.0f, mod->value);
3015 }
3016 }
3017
3018 DropModCharge(mod, spell);
3019 };
3020
3021 // Drop charges for triggering spells instead of triggered ones
3022 if (m_spellModTakingSpell)
3023 {
3024 spell = m_spellModTakingSpell;
3025 }
3026
3027 SpellModifier* chargedMod = nullptr;
3028 for (auto mod : m_spellMods[op])
3029 {
3030 // Charges can be set only for mods with auras
3031 if (!mod->ownerAura)
3032 {
3033 ASSERT(!mod->charges);
3034 }
3035
3036 if (!IsAffectedBySpellmod(spellInfo, mod, spell))
3037 {
3038 continue;
3039 }
3040
3041 if (mod->ownerAura->IsUsingCharges())
3042 {
3043 if (!chargedMod || (chargedMod->ownerAura->GetSpellInfo()->SpellPriority < mod->ownerAura->GetSpellInfo()->SpellPriority))
3044 {
3045 chargedMod = mod;
3046 }
3047
3048 continue;
3049 }
3050
3051 calculateSpellMod(mod);
3052 }
3053
3054 if (chargedMod)
3055 {
3056 calculateSpellMod(chargedMod);
3057 }
3058
3059 float diff = 0.0f;
3060 if (op == SPELLMOD_CASTING_TIME || op == SPELLMOD_DURATION)
3061 {
3062 diff = ((float)basevalue + totalflat) * (totalmul - 1.0f) + (float)totalflat;
3063 }
3064 else
3065 {
3066 diff = (float)basevalue * (totalmul - 1.0f) + (float)totalflat;
3067 }
3068
3069 basevalue = T((float)basevalue + diff);
3070 return T(diff);
3071}
3072#endif
